docs.abstract: A Minneapolis police officer slammed his vehicle into Leneal Frazier’s car while chasing a different car. His niece Darnella Frazier said his death was a “big loss” for her family.
docs.snippet: A Minneapolis police officer slammed his vehicle into Leneal Frazier’s car while chasing a different car. His niece Darnella Frazier said his death was a “big loss” for her family.
docs.lead_paragraph: For more than a year, Darnella Frazier has struggled with the trauma that came from witnessing — and recording — George Floyd’s pleas as he struggled for air under the unyielding knee of a Minneapolis police officer. Mr. Floyd was a stranger to her, but his death has haunted her ever since.

headline.main: Bystander Killed in Police Crash Is Uncle of Teen Who Filmed George Floyd’s Death
headline.print_headline: Man Killed in Police Crash Is Uncle of Teen Who Recorded Video of Floyd’s Death

docs.abstract: The league made a 10-year commitment to the Players Alliance that includes $10 million a year, plus an additional $5 million in matching contributions.
docs.snippet: The league made a 10-year commitment to the Players Alliance that includes $10 million a year, plus an additional $5 million in matching contributions.
docs.lead_paragraph: Major League Baseball announced on Monday that it would donate up to $150 million to the Players Alliance, a nonprofit formed last summer by more than 100 Black current and former players in the wake of George Floyd’s death. The donation is aimed at helping build Black participation in the sport.

headline.main: M.L.B. Pledges Millions to Build Black Participation

docs.abstract: Five years ago, players were fined for wearing unapproved shirts to protest the fatal shootings of two Black men. The league has since embraced players’ desire to speak out against social injustice.
docs.snippet: Five years ago, players were fined for wearing unapproved shirts to protest the fatal shootings of two Black men. The league has since embraced players’ desire to speak out against social injustice.
docs.lead_paragraph: On June 22, the Liberty hosted a game celebrating Juneteenth. Some players wore Black Lives Matter T-shirts during shootaround, and the night’s festivities began with a rendition of “Lift Every Voice and Sing,” often considered the national anthem of Black Americans.

headline.main: The Liberty’s Role in Making W.N.B.A. Players ‘Top Dogs’ of Activism
headline.print_headline: The Liberty Pushed for Social Justice Back When It Got Them Fined
